#Transfer data Anscombe quarter to longtable
longer <- anscombe |> 
  pivot_longer(
    cols = everything(),
    names_pattern="(.)(.)",
    names_to = c(".value","set"),
  )
print(longer)
#Caculate statistic mean and standard_deviation
longer |>
  group_by(set)|>
  summarise(mean_x=mean(x),
            mean_y=mean(y),
            sd_x=sd(x),
            sd_y=sd(y),
            cor=cor(x,y))
#Ancrombe quart plot
ggplot(longer, aes(x = x, y = y, color = set))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE)+
  facet_wrap(~set)
`geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

#combination Plot
ggplot(longer, aes(x = x, y = y, color = set))+
  geom_violin() +
  geom_point() +
  geom_boxplot() +
  facet_wrap(~set)

ggplot(crickets, aes(x=temp,y=(rate/100), color=species))+
  geom_point(size=2,
             alpha=0.8) +
  labs(x="Temperature", y="Sucess rate",
       color="Species",
       title="Crickets chirp") +
  scale_x_continuous(
    limits = c(15,32),
    breaks = seq(10,32, by =2),
    labels = function(x) paste0(x,"oC")  
    )+
  scale_y_continuous(
    limits = c(0,1.2),
    breaks = seq(0,1, by=0.1),
    labels = scales::percent)+
  geom_smooth(method="lm",se=FALSE,span =10)+

# Create example data frame
df <- data.frame(
  subject = c("A", "B", "C"),
  measurement1 = c(10, 20, 30),
  measurement2 = c(15, 25, 35),
  measurement3 = c(20, 30, 40)
)
print("Original Data Frame:")
[1] "Original Data Frame:"
print(df)
# Reshape from wide to long format
df_long1 <- df %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = starts_with("measurement"),
    names_to = "measurement",
    values_to = "value"
  )
print("Long Format Data Frame:")
[1] "Long Format Data Frame:"
print(df_long1)
?pivot_longer
# Using melt
df_long2 <- melt(df, id.vars = "subject", 
                variable.name = "measurement", 
                value.name = "value")
print(df_long2)
ggplot(df_long1,aes(x=measurement,y=value))+
  geom_bar(color="black",aes(fill = subject),stat = "identity", width = 0.5)

#OTU_table
Tab <- read_tsv("data/rhizo/otu_table.tsv",
                col_types = cols(otu_id = col_character(),
                                 .default = col_number()))
Tab
#Data_summary
dat <- Tab %>%
  pivot_longer(-otu_id, names_to = "sample_id", values_to = "count") #Transfer form wide-table to long-table
dat
#Taxa_extract
Tax <- read_tsv("data/rhizo/otu_taxonomy.tsv",
                col_types = cols(.default = "character"))
Tax
#Data_summary
dat <- dat %>%
  left_join(Tax, by = "otu_id")
dat
#Insert_metadata
Meta <- read_tsv("data/rhizo/sample_metadata.tsv",
                 col_types = cols(.default = col_character()))
Meta
#Data_summary_Final
dat <- dat %>%
  left_join(Meta, by = "sample_id")
dat
#Plot_1
dat %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_id, y = count)) +
  facet_grid(~ fraction + soil, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") + 
  geom_bar(aes(fill = Phylum), stat = "identity",, width = 1)


#Plot_1
dat %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_id, y = count)) +
  facet_grid(~ fraction + soil, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +

#Plot_2
dat %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_id, y = count)) +

dat %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_id, y = count, fill = Phylum)) +
  facet_grid(~ fraction + soil, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "fill", width = 1, color = "black") +
  geom_text(aes(label = count), position = position_fill(vjust = 0.5), size = 3) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Paired") +
  labs(
    x = "Sample ID",
    y = "Count",
    fill = "Phylum",
    title = "Stacked Bar Plot with Text Labels"
  )
#Plot_2
dat %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_id, y = count)) +
  facet_grid(~ fraction + soil, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +
  geom_bar(aes(fill = Phylum), stat = "identity", position = "fill", width = 1) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Paired")

#Trans_list_data
phyla_order <- c("Proteobacteria",
                 "Actinobacteria",
                 "Bacteroidetes",
                 "Acidobacteria",
                 "Firmicutes",
                 "Cyanobacteria",
                 "Verrucomicrobia",
                 "Gemmatimonadetes",
                 "Armatimonadetes",
                 "Chloroflexi",
                 "unclassified")
#Data_order
dat <- dat %>%
  mutate(Phylum = factor(Phylum, levels = phyla_order))
dat

#Plot_final
dat %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_id, y = count)) + #insert data x-axis;y-axis
  facet_grid(~ fraction + soil, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +
  geom_bar(aes(fill = Phylum), stat = "identity", position = "fill", width = 1) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Paired") +
  scale_y_continuous(name = "Relative abundance",
                     scale(0,1),
                     breaks = seq(0,1, by=0.2),
                     labels = scales::percent) +
  labs(title="rhizo_phylo_distribution",x="SampleID")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, size = 6),
        axis.text.y = element_text(color = "black"),
        strip.text = element_text(face = "bold"),
        strip.background = element_blank())
